      "span_text": "The latest evidence-based recommendation is that ceftriaxone should be used as an initial therapy because of its broad spectrum of action and favorable benefit-risk ratio.  For these reasons, our patient was a candidate for empiric ceftriaxone therapy after craniotomy for a very severe brain injury."
